text: Mohamed Rabbae (8 March 1941 – 17 May 2022) was a Moroccan–born Dutch politician and activist. He was born in Berrechid, French Protectorate in Morocco, Vichy France. Rabbae was a member of the House of Representatives from 1994 to 2002, and afterwards an alderman of Leiden. Rabbae died in Amersfoort, aged 81.Oud-GroenLinks-Kamerlid en minderhedenwoordvoerder Mohamed Rabbae overleden, NOS, 17 May 2022 ==References== ==Other websites== * Parlement.com biography Category:1941 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Aldermen of the Netherlands Category:Dutch activists Category:Dutch Muslims Category:Members of the House of Representatives of the Netherlands Category:GreenLeft politicians Category:Moroccan people Category:Naturalised citizens of the Netherlands
